## SpaceX Historical Events API Integration

## SpaceX Historical Events

This web application integrates with the SpaceX Historical Events API to provide users with a user-friendly interface to explore and discover SpaceX's historical milestones. Users can access a comprehensive database of SpaceX historical events, including launch details, mission objectives, and relevant articles or resources.

## Features

    Fetch and display a list of SpaceX historical events from the API.
    Sort and filter events based on event date, title, or flight number.
    Search functionality to find events based on keywords or titles.
    Display detailed information about each event, including event date, details, and relevant links to articles or resources.

## Installation

    Clone the repository: git clone example https://github.com/shel-don254/project-mode
    Navigate to the project directory: cd your-repo
    Install dependencies: npm install

## Usage

    Run the application: npm start
    Open the web browser and visit: http://localhost:3000

## Technology Stack

    Front-end: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

## API Reference

The SpaceX Historical Events API provides the data for this application. You can find more information about the API and its endpoints here.
